=Description=

"Future Earth Systems is a research organisation, examining, designing and testing future models for highly productive management of 'the common good' within and across jurisdictions.

The common good is defined as all of those activities which we need to do together for a community to thrive and live in harmony with each other and the environment.

With a focus on whole-of-government strategy, industry/sector self-sufficiency and community self-enablement, our research is looking at the macro models needed to enable truly sustainable futures.

We aim to create a deeper understanding of the productivity and sustainability challenges facing communities, industries and governments in order to drive creation of practical, testable, frameworks and systems."
(http://www.futureearthsystems.com/overview.html)

